Note that the iterative average of time series produced by algorithm 1 has the same size as the reference time series R. The algorithm 1 can be refined by iterating until no further improvement is obtained [14]. An improvement is observed when the sum of the distances (resp. similarities) between the current average R and the new pairwise average provided by KDBA, A, is lowered (resp. increased). Algorithm 2 implements this iterative strategy, which will necessarily find a local minimum
9 or will stop when a maximum number of iterations has been reached.

